    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nOne of my plugins oil.nvim doesn't behave when I do a restart with session restoration.\n\nIt would be useful for me to have this vvar so I can tell oil not do foolery when:\n`vim.v.startreason == \"restart\"`\n\nThis would be a followup on #39282, `:restart let g:startreason='restart'` did not work for me likely due to the reasons described in this [comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39282#issuecomment-4639099308)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`v:startreason` that has values `'normal'` and `'restart'`",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I believe this is a documented issue. Have you already consulted this? Are you sure this is actually related to `:restart` and not an ongoing issue?\n\nPlease consult the following links:\n\nhttps://github.com/stevearc/oil.nvim/issues/678\nhttps://github.com/stevearc/oil.nvim/issues/664\nhttps://github.com/stevearc/oil.nvim/issues/232\nhttps://github.com/barrettruth/canola.nvim/pull/195",
