        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@barrettruth I have not tested oil on session restoration _without_ restart because I don't use that in my current workflow.\n\nI have tested oil on session restoration with restart, and found that something about oil hijacking the directory buffer interferes with nvim's loading, restoring my _non-oil_ buffer with no syntax highlighting, sign column, etc. I don't think it's related to the issues you linked because the issue is present when I am viewing and restoring normal, non-oil buffers. I can confirm that building nvim off of #40186 and building oil off of this [snippet](https://github.com/nathanzeng/oil.nvim/blob/restart/lua/oil/init.lua#L813-L815), will resolve my bug.",
